Wi-fi hotspot with signalK server on Raspberry 3B/3B+

- install RaspbianOS Lite (32 or 64 bit) with rpi-imager or Balena Etcher on SD card with enabled ssh
- update RaspbianOS (sudo apt update && sudo apt full-upgrade -y)
- install signalk server (https://github.com/SignalK/signalk-server/blob/master/docs/src/installation/raspberry_pi_installation.md)
- optional: install netcat (sudo apt install netcat) to check TCP port flow with NMEA data (nc localhost 10110)
- optional: install minicom (sudo apt install minicom) to check serial ports
- install Raspap (https://raspap.com/) (SSID, IP:10.3.141.1)
- reboot with ethernet connected with router

- from another PC ssh to raspberry
- open browser in http://10.3.141.1:3000
- update signalk server software
- optional: install desired signalK plugins

